ShortDescription:
Furnished Rooms For a single person or groups.  walking distance to Cornell  University.
Corner of Eddy St. & Buffalo St. 
- Aug., 2025
LongDescription:
Furnished Rooms For a single person or groups. 
Corner of Eddy and Buffalo Street. 
A well maintained large house. 
Walking distance to Cornell University. 

Rent: $715/mo or $795/mo depending on room size.

All utilities and garbage disposal included. 
5 baths, 1 big kitchen. 
Cleaning service provided for common areas. 
Laundry on premises.

Available 8/10/2024, 12 months lease. 

Pls TEXT: Sharon 929 538 9073 (cell); 
www.gooderealtyco.com to view floor plan

ShortDescription: SUNNY, SPACIOUS, HEAT included One Bedroom & a Study Downtown! Rent $1295.00. Has internet, cable ready, has shower & full tub, close to shopping, fine dinning and entertainment.
LongDescription:
One Bedroom & a Study

- Furnished, cozy, sunny apartment downtown. 

- Plenty of windows throughout. 

- Close to the Ithaca Commons. 

-  4 mins walk to the bus stop to Cornell & Inter-city buses to NY. 

- Gas included (for heating, cooking & hot water).  

- Tenant pays for electric - cost depends on tenant's usage.

- Cable ready.
   
- High-speed internet. 

- Shower & full tub.

- Short walk to Wegmans for your grocery shopping. 

- A quiet apartment in a convenient location downtown.

ShortDescription: Recently renovated( see pictures) pet friendly,large 350 square foot studio apartment,with full kitchen and bath, 6 minutes to vet school.
LongDescription: Many veterinarian and grad students live here in this small quiet complex of 24 units. All have walk out access to a spacious 2.5 acre grounds located across the road from Fall creek. Trash, parking, water and sewer, professional  and courteous maintenance provided by the owner of 22 years, included in the rent on this updated studio apartment . Laundry on site , and bus service available. Rent w/o pets $820.00 mo, $845.00 with pets.

ShortDescription: We have rooms for rent and Sublet in Central Collegetown - 2025 Spring+Summer Excellent location for all amenities and close proximity to Cornell. Only 3 min walk to school. A great place to study.
LongDescription: We are now renting  some private, spacious, furnished rooms in our traditional student house for serious scholars . We're very centrally located with only a 3 min walk to  the Engineering or Law school. The new Cornell MBA school is on our opposite corner! corner of Linden Ave/Dryden Rd Shops and restaurants of Collegetown are also only a 2 min walk . For convenience we can't be beat.The rooms are, clean, safe, and quiet. We would love to show you around. call 607-351-1115 Katharina and Jonathan

ShortDescription: Available for 2025-2026 school year a bright and Sunny 4 window bay corner room looking unto Cornell's new MBA business school. We are  in the heart of Collegetown one block from campus.

This room has 3 large Victorian bay windows plus 1 extra.  The bay windows have a storage/window seat. The room has an oak desk, chair, bookcase, lamp, dresser and a full sized bed. This room is on the 2nd floor .
The house is a quiet traditional student house within a 3min walk to Cornell. It attracts serious mature students . 
All utilities are included.We provide free weekly cleaning of common rooms, free trash tags w/ collection, free high speed Internet along with free premium cable TV.

ShortDescription: A large nice room is available now for Spring + Summer. This is a bay window corner room right next to the Cornell business school. It's in the heart of Collegetown, one block from campus & shops.
LongDescription:
This room has a 4 tall windows including a bay window seat. It's a large room comprising of 175 square ft with a closet. It has an oak desk, chair, dresser, table and a full double bed. The room is on the first floor. It is full of sunlight and charm. This is a traditional student house within a 2-3 min walk to Cornell. It attracts serious scholars who want their quiet, private space.  We provide free trash collection, & Turbo Internet along with premium cable TV.

 3 Bed 2 Bath Upper Level Duplex ln Sapsucker Woods 

 By Cornell w/ Large Backyard 

 Sign a Lease Today
LongDescription:
RENT NOW!

Nice and quiet upper level floor of home for rent for Spring 2025 terms. The home has 3 beds and 2 baths. Located in the Sapsucker Woods area along bus stops and close to campus. The home has an attached single car garage and heat is included.  Renovation done to interior and exterior. The inside is very spacious and well maintained. The deck and backyard provide plenty of space and comfort to enjoy the outdoors when the weather is nice.

Available Now
$2513.00 a month plus utilities

ShortDescription: Studio apartment in Varna, less than 2 miles from Cornell Vet School
LongDescription: Unfurnished or partially, lower level studio in walkout ranch home. Apt includes Kitchen, bathroom with shower, livingroom/bedroom with fireplace. Free laundry accessible from the apt.  TCAT bus service in front of house.  Apartment has separate parking area and separate entrance.  Walking trails right off backyard of the property.  Utilities run ~$80/month (gas and electric).  Garbage service shared with other apt. Tenant pays for garbage tags.  Pets welcome.

ShortDescription: Clean, easy living with this 1bd. partial basement apartment available for rent in the Northeast neighborhood of Ithaca.
LongDescription: $1550/mo. includes all utilities (unlimited continuous hot water & heat) except internet and garbage tags. Quiet family of three lives above. Pets and sharing of entire yard are all negotiable. I am open to any requests and always handle a repair quickly. Friendly neighborhood close to hiking trails, Sapsucker Woods, Triphammer Marketplace, and a 5-8min drive to Cornell.

ShortDescription: Great 4 bed, 2 bath, 2 kitchen unit in Collegetown house renting for 2025-26.  Unit has 2 floors, large rooms, and off-street parking. All utilities included (except WI-FI). Located min to campus.
LongDescription:
CU! Very spacious unit in Collegetown house for the 2025-26 school year! 
Two floors with total of 4 bedrooms, 2 kitchens, and 2 bathrooms (one kitchen & bath on EACH floor), office/den/storage room, plus a nice open front yard, balcony, and private/offstreet parking). Laundry unit in house. Off street parking.

$1,250 per person/month plus WI-FI. Landlord covers gas, electric, water, trash, snow removal/lawn care.

Leasing from Aug 2025-July 2026.

ShortDescription:
Spacious 2-Bedroom, 1-Bath Furnished Rental in Quiet Neighborhood
Perfect for Faculty or Visiting Scholars
LongDescription:
This spacious 2-bedroom, 1-bath home offers 1200+ sq ft of furnished living space with an open floor plan. The spacious living and dining areas provide ample room for both work and relaxation. Situated in a quiet neighborhood on Eastern Heights Drive, its a 6-minute drive to Cornell and on the TCAT 51 bus route. Ideal for faculty or visiting scholars. Access to the backyard and private deck with serene views.

Available for short or long-term leases.

ShortDescription:
5 Bed 4 Bath Single Family Home 
10 Minutes from Cornell Vet School
LongDescription: Nestled next to Cornell University and the Cornell Vet School, Observatory Circle in Ithaca, NY, offers luxurious 3,200 sq ft paired homes. Each home features high ceilings, expansive glass windows, and breathtaking views. Located near Varna, Dryden Rd., and Flat Rock, this community provides access to scenic hiking trails through lush forests. These spacious single-family homes boast 5 bedrooms, 4 baths, and a garage, seamlessly blending comfort with the serene beauty of upstate New York.

ShortDescription: A three-story single-family house located in Cornell Fall Creek neighborhood
LongDescription:
Four furnished private rooms are available for the new semester
 Walking distance to Cornell campus through Suspension Bridge
 Less than 2 minutes walking distance to Johnson Museum of Art
 12-month lease starts from $750 to $1150 (depending on room location/size and private full bathroom access)
 All utilities are included in the rent
 Access to washer and dryer
 Shared kitchen with two fridges/freezers and commercial cooking stove and washing sink

ShortDescription: Beautifully renovated 2 room /1 bath Apt Across from West Campus
LongDescription:
Newly and totally renovated!!
This unit is perfect for one or two tenants as it can be used as a 2bd or 1bd/den apt, across from West Campus

Brand new stainless steel appliances, floor, kitchen and bathroom! Fully furnished or not- as you wish :-)  We can provide an additional bed / shelves, let us know, we try to accomodate.

Included: 
-Internet 
-Gas
-Water/sewer
-Snow & lawn maintenance
-Garbage pickup

* Tenants pays electric*

ShortDescription:
2025 SPRING SUBLET - Ithaca Commons Private Room
Private a 3-bed-2-bath apartment. The monthly rent includes all utilities besides electricity. Indoor washer&dryer, furniture provided. Female only.
LongDescription: I am subletting this spacious, fully furnished apartment starting Spring 2025, and its perfectly situated in the heart of Downtown Ithaca at the Commons. Youll be just a short walk from the best bars, cafes, and restaurants, with a bus stop conveniently across the street. Enjoy the convenience of in-door laundry and available parking. It also offers great amenities like 24/7 maintenance, internet, a secure entrance, and a rooftop terrace. If you're interested, reach out to st678@cornell.edu

ShortDescription: Motivated sublet! Entire apartment in The Ithacan. 1 bed, 1 bath + office, furnished. Stainless steel, W/D, walk-in closet. Rooftop terrace, gym, business lounge. Available to June 2025.
LongDescription:
Avoid a 12-month lease and save on summer rent! Take over my furnished 1BR/1BA Ithacan Residences sublet until June 2025. Rent will range from $2000-2900/month depending on lease start date. Enjoy in-unit washer/dryer, stainless steel appliances, walk-in closet, and a flexible office space. Building boasts rooftop terrace, gym, business lounge, and more.
In-unit laundry. The apartment is located on the 8th floor, ensuring ample natural light as it's positioned above the adjacent parking garage.

ShortDescription: Spacious, fully furnished apartment in a prime location just minutes from Cornell University. Features modern amenities, a gym, laundry, and a well-equipped kitchen. Ready for move in!
LongDescription: Looking for a prime location near Cornell? Sublease my 3-bedroom apartment at 327 Eddy Street, Apartment 2B for $3,600/month ($1,200/room, negotiable). The fully furnished unit includes a gym, laundry, private key access, and a well-equipped kitchen with modern appliances. Each bedroom features a queen-size bed, desk, dresser, and wardrobe. Sublease available JanuaryMay 2025 with an official agreement.

ShortDescription: Master bedroom with private bathroom/shower available in 2bd/2b home

Master bedroom with a private bathroom/shower available in 2bd/2b manufactured home, east side of campus (~5-min drive). $1000/month includes all utilities (electricity, water, trash, Wi-Fi, parking). *only friendly cats allowed, no dogs*

Amenities: furnished (twin bed, desk, dresser), in-unit laundry, walk-in closet, shared kitchen and utilities/tools, walk-in shower, free parking, near bus stops. 

Flexible lease terms. Roommate is a friendly 2nd-year vet student with a small dog and cat.

Both roommates are very quiet, no party.
All bills are included in the rent.

ShortDescription: *1 room available* Penthouse 602 is a fully furnished, 4-bed 2-bath unit in the heart of Collegetown. On the top floor, it offers privacy, stunning views, in building washer/dryer, and fitness room.
LongDescription: Penthouse Apartment 602 at 205 Dryden Rd is a 4-bed, 2-bath fully furnished unit. Located on the top floor, it offers privacy, natural light, and excellent views. The spacious layout includes 4 furnished bedrooms (*1 available*), a living area, and modern finishes. The secure building has on-site laundry and is within short walking distance of Cornell University, restaurants, and shops in Collegetown. The sublet provides a desirable option for students seeking housing close to campus.

ShortDescription: 4 Bedroom apartment with 1.5 bathrooms with 1 room available somewhere on the 2nd to 5th floor.
LongDescription: 4 Bedroom apartment with 1.5 bathrooms with 1 room available somewhere on the 2nd to 5th floor. The location is very close to west campus with buses available. The other 3 tenants will all be junior female students at the time of the lease. The apartment complex has washing machines and dryers. The apartment has a kitchen, common room, and television. It is fully furnished. Each room has a window, desk, chair, and either full or twin bed. Electricity is not included in the rent.

ShortDescription: Beautiful furnished stand-alone Carriage House in the quaint tree-lined Henry St. John historic neighborhood.
LongDescription: This 1884 Carriage House was completely renovated in 2019 into a cozy, modern, and comfortable home. It boasts white oak hardwood floors, modern kitchen with all amenities, first floor half bath, second floor large bedroom with king bed, full bath, and washer/dryer. The home has both heat and air conditioning wall units on both floors. A few original windows and wood beams add to the charm and character of the space.

ShortDescription: Furnished and spacious, 2200 sq. ft. 6 Bedroom, 2 Bath home near everything.
LongDescription: Fully furnished, spacious, 2200 sq. ft. 6-Bedroom, 2-Bathroom Apartment near everything. A 5 minute walk to Downtown, 10 minute walk to Collegetown and a few hundred feet from the footbridge to South Hill. Three bedrooms have queen-sized beds, and three have full-sized and each room has it's own heating and cooling controls. It has an in apartment washer and dryer, high speed internet, backyard and nice front porch. We also provide a cleaner a couple times a month to clean common spaces.

ShortDescription: Room available for sublet until May 18, 2025 in furnished Ithaca home, walking distance from Cornell's campus and Ithaca Commons. Renovated kitchen with stainless appliances, heat, A/C, and laundry.
LongDescription:
Sublet is for one beautifully furnished, light-filled bedroom and shared common space, including kitchen, living room, family room, dining room, and sunroom. Tall ceilings, classic Victorian details, formal entry, & Lodge-style sunroom. Distant views of West Hill from all three stories.

Wooden fencing encloses the backyard with stone patio and kitchen garden.

Email current Cornell graduate student at jab865@Cornell.edu.

Subject to landlord approval. Friendly dog on premises some of the time.

ShortDescription: Room available from March to May, just a 5-7 minute walk to Collegetown and Cornell via Hoy Road. Great location for students. The room shares a kitchen and bathroom with three housemates.
LongDescription:
Looking for someone to take over my lease from March to May. This cozy room is in an ideal location, just a 5-7 minute walk to Collegetown and conveniently close to Cornell University via Hoy Roadperfect for students or anyone visiting the university.

The room is on a shared floor with three other housemates. It features:

Three large windows overlooking the side yard with morning sunlight.
A shared kitchen and bathroom.
This is a great opportunity for anyone looking for temporary housing.
